kely. AGN hosts show smaller masses in clusters for Seyferts and\nTransition objects, which might be due to gas stripping. In voids, the AGN\npopulation is dominated by the most massive galaxy hosts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 20 Oct 2017 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Dec 2017 10:06:41 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2018 12:16:05 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 15 Jan 2018 13:58:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-18"}
